# Tokezly — optional environment overrides. Copy to .env and fill in as needed.
# Per-user cloud API keys are normally entered in-app (Settings + the OS keychain).
# This file is for build/dev overrides and the optional bundled free-cloud key.

# Directory containing libclang.dll, used when building the Whisper engine from source.
# On Windows you can install it (and cmake) user-scope with:  pip install libclang cmake
# LIBCLANG_PATH=C:\path\to\libclang

# Optional: bake a Google Gemini (AI Studio free tier) key into the build so the
# "free cloud" rewrite engine works with no per-user setup. Get one at
# https://aistudio.google.com/apikey . On-device stays the privacy default; the
# free tier is used by Google for training, so this is an explicit opt-in.
# WARNING: a baked key is shared by every install and extractable from the binary
# (~1500 req/day per key, and sharing it breaks Google's ToS). Fine for private
# builds only — public releases should use per-user keys or a proxy.
# TOKEZLY_GEMINI_API_KEY=
